description: Sabo Suya was opened in November 2010 in Houston Texas with the goal of publicizing homemade suya that was being made privately among family and friends. Each suya is lovingly and carefully handmade from beef, chicken, ram, lamb or fish and natural ingredients, duplicating what obtains in Northern Nigeria. Word about this suya quickly spread, and it was soon introduced to people of diverse ethnicities and cultures in southwest Houston, and now across the United States, Canada and the Atlantic. Sabo Suya is open every day, providing hundreds of suya and entrees to people in person and through local, national and international deliveries. No one is ever a stranger here.
